        "q1": "What is THCa, and how does it differ from THC?",
        "a1": "THCa (tetrahydrocannabinolic acid) is a non-psychoactive cannabinoid found in raw cannabis. When heated through smoking or vaping, it converts to THC — the compound responsible for the psychoactive effect. Our products contain THCa, ensuring compliance with federal regulations while delivering the desired effects upon use.",
        "q2": "What's inside a Sundaze hash hole pre-roll?",
